thread.title: Grain lower, livestock lower

title: Grain lower, livestock lower
text:
Sat, Sep 12, 2015, 1:15 AM AEST - Australia Markets closed Grain lower, livestock lower Grain lower on the CBOT, beef lower and pork lower on the CME Associated Press – 27 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were lower in early trading Friday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for December delivery lost 4 cents to $4.74 a bushel; December corn was 4 cents lower at $3.7020 a bushel; December oats were .25 cent lower at 2.3160 a bushel; while November soybeans lost 5.50 cents to 8.6820 a bushel. 
Beef was lower and pork was lower on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. 
December live cattle was 1.08 cents lower at $1.4363 a pound; October feeder cattle was 1.50 cents lower at $1.970 a pound; December lean hogs lost .78 cent to $.6278 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Woolworths boss takes a pay cut AAP
